metadata.title: Piper PA-28 Cherokee
aws::graph::propositions: Piper PA-28 Cherokee Aircraft Variants
Piper PA-28 Cherokee is produced in Archer DX trainer variant.
Piper PA-28 Cherokee is produced in Archer DLX personal aircraft variant.
PA-28-181 Pilot 100 is a version of Piper PA-28 Cherokee.
PA-28-181 Pilot 100i is a version of Piper PA-28 Cherokee.
PA-28-181 Pilot 100 and PA-28-181 Pilot 100i were introduced in 2019.
PA-28-181 Pilot 100 is intended as a low cost VFR trainer.
PA-28-181 Pilot 100i is intended as a low cost IFR trainer.
PA-28-181 Pilot 100 and PA-28-181 Pilot 100i are intended for the flight training market.
PA-28-181 Pilot 100 and PA-28-181 Pilot 100i have fixed landing gear.
PA-28-181 Pilot 100 and PA-28-181 Pilot 100i have a 180 hp Lycoming IO-360-B4A engine.
PA-28-181 Pilot 100 and PA-28-181 Pilot 100i have Garmin G3X Touch Certified avionics.
PA-28-181 Pilot 100i includes GFC500 autopilot.
PA-28-181 Pilot 100 and PA-28-181 Pilot 100i feature a 2-side-window fuselage.
PA-28-181 Pilot 100 and PA-28-181 Pilot 100i feature a tapered wing.
PA-28-181 Pilot 100 and PA-28-181 Pilot 100i have no baggage door.
PA-28-181 Pilot 100 and PA-28-181 Pilot 100i have no air conditioning.
PA-28-181 Pilot 100 and PA-28-181 Pilot 100i have no instruments on the right-hand panel.
PA-28-181 Pilot 100 and PA-28-181 Pilot 100i have all-white paint with decals.
PA-28-181 Pilot 100 has two-place seating as standard.
PA-28-181 Pilot 100i has a rear third seat with push-to-talk as standard.
PA-28-181 Pilot 100i has Bluetooth functions as standard.
A rear third seat with push-to-talk and Bluetooth functions is optional on PA-28-181 Pilot 100.
PA-28-181 Pilot 100 and PA-28-181 Pilot 100i were type certified in the United States in December 2020.
PA-28-181 Pilot 100 and PA-28-181 Pilot 100i were type certified in Europe in August 2021.

text:
Produced in Archer DX trainer and Archer DLX personal aircraft variants.
PA-28-181 Pilot 100 and Pilot 100i
New versions introduced in 2019 intended as low cost VFR and IFR trainers respectively, for the flight training market. Fixed landing gear, 180 hp Lycoming IO-360-B4A, Garmin G3X Touch Certified avionics. IFR version includes GFC500 autopilot. Features the 2-side-window fuselage with the later tapered wing, no baggage door, no air conditioning, no instruments on right-hand panel, all-white paint with decals, two-place seating standard on 100, rear third seat with push-to-talk and Bluetooth functions standard on 100i and optional on 100. These new versions were type certified in the US in December 2020 and in Europe in August 2021.
